label.value: area under the anorectal pressure curve

value.value: This measurement involves calculation of the the area under the plotted curve for pressure generated by anorectal contractions.

label.value: red blood cell sodium level

value.value: The intracellular concentration of sodium ions measured in a specific sample of red blood cells.

label.value: red blood cell potassium level

value.value: The intracellular concentration of potassium ions measured in a specific sample of red blood cells

label.value: red blood cell ATP level

value.value: The intracellular concentration of adenosine-5'- triphosphate measured in a specific sample of red blood cells.

label.value: red blood cell Na-K-Cl cotransport activity

value.value: Measurement of the level of activity of the erythrocyte membrane transport protein that transports sodium (Na), potassium (K), and chloride (Cl) ions across the cell membrane into erythrocytes. For every sodium and potassium ion transported, this symporter transports two chloride ions, thus maintaining electroneutrality.

label.value: red blood cell sodium/potassium passive permeability

value.value: This is a measurement of sodium and/or potassium ion efflux from erythrocytes in the presence of a sodium-potassium pump inhibitor (ouabain) and a sodium-potassium-chloride cotransporter inhibitor (furosemide or bumetamide).

label.value: number of small metastatic liver tumors in the right liver

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of small (< 1 mm) metastatic tumors in the right lobes (right lobes and caudate lobes) of the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: number of small metastatic liver tumors in the left liver

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of small (< 1 mm) metastatic tumors in the left lobes (left lateral lobe and median lobes in rat) of the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: small liver metastatic tumorous lesion diameter measurement

value.value: The distance (< 1 mm) between two specified opposite points on the periphery of a micrometastatic tumorous lesion found on or in the liver. A micrometastatic tumorous lesion is one that is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: large liver metastatic tumorous lesion diameter measurement

value.value: The distance (> 3 mm) between two specified opposite points on the periphery of a macrometastatic tumorous lesion found on or in the liver. A macrometastatic tumorous lesion is one that is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cells.

label.value: medium-sized liver metastatic tumorous lesion diameter measurement

value.value: The distance ( 1-3 mm) between two specified opposite points on the periphery of a micrometastatic tumorous lesion found on or in the liver. A micrometastatic tumorous lesion is one that is or has the potential to become a tumor, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of tissue in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive. Tumorous lesions include tumors, preneoplastic lesions, and hyperplastic lesions composed of histologically normal cell

label.value: percentage of study population developing peritoneal carcinomatosis during a period of time

value.value: The total number of subjects within a study population which develop peritoneal carcinomatosis during a specified period of time divided by the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage. Peritoneal carcinomatosis is multiple tumorsusually metastatic, growing in or on the peritoneum, a serous membrane that lines the peritoneal cavity .

label.value: number of large metastatic liver tumors in the left liver

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of large ( > 3 mm) metastatic tumors in the left lobes (left lateral lobe and median lobes in rat) of the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: number of large metastatic liver tumors in the right liver

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of large (> 3 mm) metastatic tumors in the right lobes (right lobes and caudate lobes) of the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: pancreatic islet insulin output

value.value: A calculated measure of the amount of insulin secretion from a single pancreatic islet per unit of time.

label.value: percentage of study population developing ascites during a period of time

value.value: The total number of subjects within a study population which develop ascites during a specified period of time divided by the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage. Ascites is the pathological accumulation or retention of free fluid within the peritoneal cavity.

label.value: percentage of study population developing extra-hepatic metastases during a period of time

value.value: The number of subjects developing extra-hepatic metastases in a study population during a certain period compared to the total number of subjects in the study population, expressed as a percentage. An extra-hepatic metastasis is a neoplasm transferred from one organ or part of the body to another (not liver) remote from the primary site.

label.value: calculated blood CD25 cell count

value.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the number of lymphocytes expressing the CD25 antigen on their surface in a specified sample of blood.

label.value: debris zone thickness

value.value: Measurement of the thickness of a buildup of an autofluorescent layer containing the nonphagocytosed photoreceptor outer segment (POS) debris in the subretinal space of subjects with retinal disease. The debris zone is located between the outer nuclear layer (ONL) and the retinal pigmented epithelium (RPE).

label.value: percentage of 13 cm2 floor sectors crossed into, out of or within a discrete space in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The percentage of equilateral right-angled grid elements measuring 3.6 centimeters on a side traversed by an experimental subject into, out of or within a distinct and specified area of an experimental apparatus (especially such a movement accomplished by the action of appendages such as flagella, limbs, or wings) originated, undertaken, controlled, or accomplished as a result of free will or choice.

label.value: time to first grooming within an experimental apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the latency period spent by an organism or experimental subject in the initial occupied space before starting any activity of self-cleaning or cleaning another subject.

label.value: amount of time spent making rearing movements in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The total amount of time in an experiment that a quadrupedal subject spends in a distinct and specified area of a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose, rising up on its back legs.

label.value: time to first rearing within an experimental apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the latency period spent by an organism or experimental subject in the initial occupied space before a quadrupedal subject begins rising up on its back legs.

label.value: head movement measurement

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the motion of the head which originated, or was undertaken, controlled, or accomplished as a result of an organism's free will or choice.

label.value: head dip measurement

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to a downward motion of the head which originated, or was undertaken, controlled, or accomplished as a result of an organism's free will or choice.

label.value: number of head dipping movements in an experimental apparatus

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of how many times a quadrupedal subject in a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose moves its head purposefully in a downward motion.

label.value: time to first head dip within an experimental apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the latency period spent by an subject in the initial occupied space before starting any intentional downward motion of the head.

label.value: amount of time spent making head dipping movements in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The total amount of time in an experiment that a subject spends in a distinct and specified area of a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose, making intentional downward movements of its head.

label.value: number of glomeruli per kidney

value.value: The number of glomeruli calculated to be in one kidney from a measured sample of that kidney. Glomeruli are the tufts of capillaries each situated within a Bowman's capsule at the end of a renal tubule in the vertebrate kidney that filter waste products from the blood and thus initiate urine formation.

label.value: calculated kidney glomerulus count

value.value: Any count that has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the glomeruli of one or both kidneys, the paired organ which functions to maintain proper water and electrolyte balance, regulate acid-base concentration, and filter the blood of metabolic wastes.

label.value: number of glomeruli per volume of kidney

value.value: A count that has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the glomeruli in a given volume of kidney tissue.

label.value: ratio of deaths related to chronic hypertension to total study population during a period of time

value.value: A measure of the total number of deaths related to chronic hypertension occurring during a specified period of time within a study population divided by the total number of individuals in the study population and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: ratio of deaths related to mammary cancer to total study population during a period of time

value.value: A measure of the total number of deaths related to mammary cancer occurring during a specified period of time within a study population divided by the total number of individuals in the study population and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: ratio of deaths related to experimental autoimmune encephalomyelitis to total study population during a period of time

value.value: A measure of the total number of deaths related to experimental autoimmune encephalomyelitis occurring during a specified period of time within a study population divided by the total number of individuals in the study population and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: ratio of survivors of metabolic syndrome to total study population during a period of time

value.value: This is a measure of the total number of metabolic syndrome subjects within a study population which remain alive during a specified period of time divided by the total number of individuals in the study population, presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: amount of time spent making stretched-attend posture movements in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The total amount of time in an experiment that a quadrupedal subject spends in a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose, making stretched-attend posture movements, in which the hind legs remain stationary while the body is stretched forward with head raised.

label.value: time to first stretched-attend posture movement within an experimental apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the latency period spent by an subject in the initial occupied space of an experimental apparatus before starting any stretched-attend posture movement.

label.value: exploratory movement measurement

value.value: A measurement of time, movement type, or location of a subject's exploration of an object, location, or other entity.

label.value: amount of time spent exploring a novel object in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The total amount of time in an experiment that a subject spends in a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose, exploring a novel object.

label.value: amount of time spent exploring a familiar object in an experimental apparatus

value.value: The total amount of time in an experiment that a subject spends in a piece of technical equipment or machinery, an appliance, or a device designed for a particular purpose, exploring a familiar object.

label.value: ratio of deaths related to DMBA toxicity to total study population during a period of time

value.value: A measure of the total number of deaths related to 7,12-Dimethylbenz(a)anthracene (DMBA) toxicity occurring during a specified period of time within a study population divided by the total number of individuals in the study population and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: ratio of deaths related to left ventricular hypertrophy to total study population during a period of time

value.value: A measure of the total number of deaths related to left ventricular hypertrophy occurring during a specified period of time within a study population divided by the total number of individuals in the study population and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: renal cortex morphological measurement

value.value: Measurement of the physical form or structure of the renal cortex, the outer part of the kidney, composed mainly of glomeruli and convoluted tubules.

label.value: renal cortex cross-sectional area

value.value: A measurement of the outer extent of a plane perpendicular through the hilum, the opening on the medial margin of the kidney leading into the renal sinus. Its value may be calculated from or measured via a microscopic image.

label.value: carotid artery blood flow velocity

value.value: Measurement of average carotid artery blood flow velocity, the speed with which blood moves along the circulation in any particular segment of carotid artery. Blood flow velocity is related directly to blood flow and inversely to cross-sectional area. Blood flow velocity can be measured indirectly by Doppler ultrasound

label.value: peak carotid artery blood flow velocity

value.value: Measurement of peak carotid artery blood flow velocity, the top speed (systolic) with which blood moves along the circulation in any particular segment of carotid artery. Blood flow velocity is related directly to blood flow and inversely to cross-sectional area. Blood flow velocity can be measured indirectly by Doppler ultrasound

label.value: cerebral blood flow rate

value.value: Cerebral blood flow (CBF) rate is the volume of blood delivered to or exiting the brain, through a network of cerebral arteries and veins, per unit time

label.value: number of blastocysts implanted per litter

value.value: This is the number, i.e., the quantity determined by count, of implanted blastocysts, products of one gestation produced during one pregnancy in a multiparous mammal.

label.value: number of fetuses with external malformations to total number of live fetuses ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the number of fetuses with external malformations is divided by the total number of live fetuses in the prospective litter, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated offspring mortality measurement

value.value: Any measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the number of dead offspring in a litter or prospective litter. A litter or prospective litter refers to the products of one gestation produced by a multiparous mammal.
